# Resolution 2013-03-14.bg.1: OpenEmbedded as associated project

This resolution was adopted by the Board of Directors of SPI at their
meeting of [March 14, 2013](/meetings/minutes/2013/2013-03-14/).

WHEREAS

1. OpenEmbedded is a substantial and significant Free Software project.

2. The OpenEmbedded developers would like SPI's support and assistance,
   including taking donations.

THE SPI BOARD RESOLVES THAT

3. OpenEmbedded is formally invited to become an SPI Associated Project,
   according to the SPI Framework for Associated Projects, SPI Resolution
   1998-11-16.iwj.1-amended-2004-08-10.iwj.1, a copy of which can be found
   at [https://www.spi-inc.org/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/](/corporate/resolutions/2004/2004-08-10.iwj.1/)

4. Philip Balister &lt;philip@balister.org&gt; is recognised by SPI as the
   authoritative decision maker and SPI liaison for OpenEmbedded.
   Successors will be appointed by the OpenEmbedded eV board
   &lt;board@openembedded.org&gt;.

5. This invitation will lapse, if not accepted, 60 days after it is
   approved by the SPI Board.

